Repeals and reenactments.— Laws 2023, ch. 118, § 1 repealed former 32A-11-1 NMSA 1978 and enacted a new section.

Contingent effective dates.— The effective date of the provisions of Laws 2023, ch. 118, § 1 shall become effective when the thirty-fifth state has enacted the Revised Interstate Compact on the Placement of Children as provided in Section B of Article 14 of the Revised Interstate Compact on the Placement of Children. The secretary of children, youth and families shall notify the governor, the executive director of the New Mexico compilation commission and the director of the legislative council service when the thirty-fifth state has enacted the Revised Interstate Compact on the Placement of Children.
